news.title: For halting action on builder, babu gets MahaRERA summons
news.para: In a controversial move, the Mumbai suburban collector's office has halted the auction of Jawahar Talkies compound in Mulund despite a warrant from real estate regulator MahaRERA to attach and sell the property belonging to Nirmal Developers for defaulting on payments to home buyers.

news.title: Shriram Properties acquires three companies
news.para: 1,000 equity shares of Shriram Living Spaces, Shriram Upscale Spaces and Shrivision Elevation have been acquired of Rs 10 each, the company said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Big relief to builders as Andhra Pradesh government withdraws GO-145
news.para: The state government had issued the GO in December, 2021 through which it wanted to take 5 per cent of any private layout for allocation of house sites to the economically weaker sections (EWS).

news.title: Nagpur: Unauthorized plots, buildings on 14,000 reserved plots apply for regularization
news.para: agpur Improvement Trust (NIT) has rejected most of these applications citing Nagpur bench of Bombay high court verdicts, but is ready to regularize them in case Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) drops reservation in city’s development plan (DP) currently under preparation.

news.title: MREAT sets aside MahaRERA order on realty portals' listing as agents
news.para: The web portals had challenged this order stating that they were not facilitating any sale, but merely were providing information via advertisements to the public.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government nod to 239 Amrut projects in 106 ULBs
news.para: The state government had granted administrative approval for Rs.3151 crore to complete the proposed projects in 106 urban local bodies.

news.title: DLF's net profit up 36.48% in Q3 FY23
news.para: DLF's 's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,559.66 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 7.54 per cent from Rs 1,686.92 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body to divide bulk lands into small bits
news.para: The VMRDA has been accorded the required administrative approvals to go ahead with this during the recent meeting, chaired by special chief secretary (municipal administration and urban development) Y Sri Lakshmi, to ‘increase the saleability’ of these lands.

news.title: Embassy Office Parks REIT's net profit dips 21.62% in Q3 FY23
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services, manager to Embassy Office Parks REIT, declared distribution of Rs 503.33 crore/ Rs 5.31 per unit for the quarter ended December 31, 2022.

news.title: Vodafone sells British headquarter, rents part instead amid downsizing
news.para: ​Iqon Capital agreed to buy the total of seven buildings known as “The Connection” on behalf of Aljazira Capital for an undisclosed figure, it said in a statement on Tuesday.

news.title: Bhopal civic body to appoint private agency to boost property tax collection
news.para: The new system is a first-of-a-kind model to be adopted by a municipal corporation. The existing system of revenue collection by wards and zone offices will continue, he added.

news.title: Now, apply online for stamp duty assessment in Gujarat
news.para: With an overwhelming number of applicants outside the office of the deputy collector (stamp duty assessment), the revenue department has made the process online from Tuesday.

news.title: Gurugram: Residents seek ban on fourth floors in colonies citing infra burden
news.para: Earlier this month, the Supreme Court banned multi-storey apartments on residential plots in Chandigarh, following which RWAs in Panchkula demanded a similar ban on construction of stilt-plus four floors in their areas.

news.title: Two bedroom flat in Chandigarh sector 51 goes for Rs 1.1 crore
news.para: The CHB had put up 49 freehold dwelling units and 91 leasehold commercial units for e-auction in different sectors. ​​The last date for submission of bids was Tuesday. The CHB generated Rs 6.34 crore against reserve price of Rs 5.72 crore.

news.title: Two-thirds of flat owners' nod OK for redevelopment: Tamil Nadu law
news.para: The new law, which will come into effect the day the state government notifies the rules, has some sweeping provisions. For instance, an apartment complex having more than four dwelling units should have an association and there shall be only one association for each such complex.
